dsr1: I might be willing to try eating monkey meat, under some circumstances
It would bother me to be in a science class, and to see a human hand preserved in a jar
It bothers me to hear someone clear a throat full of mucous
I never let any part of my body touch the toilet seat in public restrooms.
I would go out of my way to avoid walking through a graveyard.
Seeing a cockroach in someone else's house doesn't bother me.
It would bother me tremendously to touch a dead body.
If I see someone vomit, it makes me sick to my stomach.
I probably would not go to my favorite restaurant if I found out that the cook had a cold.

It would not upset me at all to watch a person with a glass eye take the eye 
out of the socket.
It would bother me to see a rat run across my path in a park.
I would rather eat a piece of fruit than a piece of paper

Even if I was hungry, I would not drink a bowl of my favorite soup if it had been
stirred by a used but thoroughly washed flyswatter.

It would bother me to sleep in a nice hotel room if I knew that a man had died of a
heart attack in that room the night before.

dsr_e: You see maggots on a piece of meat in an outdoor garbage pail.
You see a person eating an apple with a knife and fork
While you are walking through a tunnel under a railroad track, you smell urine.

You take a sip of soda, and then realize that you drank from the glass that an
 		acquaintance of yours had been drinking from
Your friend's pet cat dies, and you have to pick up the dead body with your bare hands.
You see someone put ketchup on vanilla ice cream, and eat it.
You see a man with his intestines exposed after an accident.
You discover that a friend of yours changes underwear only once a week.
A friend offers you a piece of chocolate shaped like dog doo.
You accidentally touch the ashes of a person who has been cremated.
You are about to drink a glass of milk when you smell that it is spoiled.

As part of a sex education class, you are required to inflate a new unlubricated
		condom, using your mouth.
You are walking barefoot on concrete, and you step on an earthworm.

pol_ques: The government should pass a Constitutional amendment that would make it illegal to discriminate against anyone in any situation based on sexual orientation.
The national government should establish a centrally funded medical program so that all persons, regardless of means, have access to medical care.
It should be legal and constitutional to say a prayer at the beginning of assemblies in public schools.
Persons should be allowed to join and serve in the military regardless of their sexual preference as long as their behavior meets strict military standards.
A person should be able to use and grow small quantities of marijuana in the privacy of his or her own home with no legal consequences.
Persons receiving the death penalty should be limited in their number of appeals, and the death sentence should be carried out in a shorter time period than it is now.
The government should reverse its decision on abortion and make it more challenging to have an abortion except in special cases such as rape and incest.
India should require one year of military service for all able-bodied people.
Parents should be able to send their children to any school they choose, and tax money should be used to support the schools that parents choose.
Police should be able to confiscate any materials that are deemed to be obscene or pornographic.
The central government should be required to have a balanced budget that does not spend more than the money that comes in from taxes
Laws that limit the sale of fireworks and other explosive materials that are not intended for legitimate cultural or religious purposes should be passed.
Sex education should be in taught all public schools and all students should be required to take the class unless exempted by parents.
Reservation system should be abolished in India.
The Prime Minister, without permission from the President, should be able to use the armed forces and call for an emergency in possible combat areas for as long as he/she deems necessary.
Laws should be passed to make it legal for public employees such as police, firemen, teachers, and garbage collectors to go on strike.
Public schools should be required to teach the world's creation as written in the Bhagavad Gita in all classes that teach evolution theory.
The government should mandate family planning counseling and reversible sterilization for low-income, unmarried women with three or more children.
Birth control information, non-prescription contraceptive devices, and the morning-after pill should be made available on college campuses.
Evidence gathered by the police, even if an honest mistake was made in getting a warrant, should be used to help prosecute suspected criminals.
Inter-religious marriages should be abolished.
Requirements for any military duty, including combat, should be based on physical, emotional, and intellectual abilities, not gender or sexual orientation.
The law should make private employers hire minorities if they are qualified because they have been victims of discrimination in the past.
Certain literature should be banned from city libraries if the librarian feels it is improper or too controversial.
The government should interfere during conversion from one religion to another.
The government should spend less on the military and more on education and the environment.
India should not trade with or help any nation that violates human rights.
People planning to get married should have a mandatory test for STDs such as AIDS and gonorrhea before a marriage certificate can be issued.
There are too many lawsuits in the courts, and the courts do not have the time to deal with more severe issues.
Nuclear power and nuclear-generating stations should be banned.
The death penalty is clearly a form of cruel and unusual punishment and should be banned.
Sexual harassment of women in the workplace is a serious problem and should be prosecuted under law
The primary function of prisons should be to rehabilitate criminals, not to punish them.
The states should abolish criminal penalties for victimless crimes such as gambling and prostitution.
The CBI should be able to wiretap the phones and read the mail of suspected individuals.
The central government must take strong steps to reverse global warming, even if it means losing some jobs.
Most youth who fall under the reservation scheme today are lazy and do not want to work.
Profanity and sexually oriented material on television should be stopped or penalized by the government.
The government must stop the flow of immigrants, both legal and illegal, from Bangladesh.
There should be sensitization classes for individuals in the LGBTQ+ community in school.
